  nine species (H2 O2 H O OH HO2 H2O2 water N2) in data/standards/components/
  (their gibbsFormation + idealGasHeatCapacity, each individually cited).  So
  the WHERE-it-ends-up is curated physics; only the HOW-FAST is illustrative.

  THE STRUCTURE (the part that teaches): a slow initiation builds a trace
  radical pool; chain BRANCHING (R2, R3, R5 — one radical in, two out) then
  outruns termination (R6, R9), the radical population explodes, and the heat
